  <section class="hero">
    <img src="uploads/new-logo.png" alt="Sonic Sentinel logo" class="logo" />
    <h2>Sonic Sentinel Saga</h2>
    <h3>Sound is Sacred</h3>
    <div class="tagline">Signal of the Sentinel · Rebirth of the Sentinel · Legacy of the Sentinel</div>
  </section>

  <section class="story-section">
    <h2 class="section-title">The Story</h2>
    <p class="story-summary">In a digital world, an unknown signal awakens: the Sentinel. At first just a pulse sowing chaos, it later rises from the silence as a force that unites humanity. In the end, the Sentinel becomes a mythical legend — a presence that never vanishes, but lives on as an eternal echo of music and light.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2 class="section-title">About</h2>
    <p>Sonic Sentinel is a concept-driven electronic music project that explores the intersection of sound, energy, and emotion. Blending elements of progressive house, melodic techno, and cinematic EDM, the project creates sonic landscapes that feel both futuristic and primal. Each track is a transmission—each set a signal—from a world where sound is sacred, and rhythm is power.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Albums -->
  <main class="albums-wrap">
    <h2 class="section-title">Albums</h2>
    <section class="albums-grid">
      <!-- Album 1 -->
      <article class="card">
        <div class="cover">
          <img src="uploads/album1.png" alt="Signal of the Sentinel cover">
        </div>
        <div class="content">
          <div class="album-desc">
            In the shadows of a digital world, an unknown signal emerges. It begins as a pulse – <strong>Transmission</strong> – crawling through the networks. 
            As the waves grow stronger, disturbances arise (<strong>System Breach</strong>), unexplained phenomena surface, 
            and a growing awareness forms of a hidden order: a guardian. The Sentinel. 
            Its presence feels like a command, a <strong>Core Directive</strong>, but also a looming threat. 
            What first seemed like mere waves and glitches escalates into catastrophe (<strong>Frequency Collapse</strong>). 
            Yet one certainty remains: the signal is alive. It is the message of the Sentinel itself.
          </div>
          <a href="#" class="listen-btn">Listen</a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Album 2 -->
      <article class="card">
        <div class="cover">
          <img src="uploads/album2.png" alt=“Rebirth of the Sentinel cover">
        </div>
        <div class="content">
          <div class="album-desc">
            After the collapse, silence returns – but silence never lasts. 
            From the ashes, a new force rises (<strong>Second Dawn</strong>). 
            The signal is heard again, but this time by humanity. Across the world, the echo of the Sentinel resonates: 
            in sorrow (<strong>Sentinel’s Cry</strong>), in celebration (<strong>Summer of Rave</strong>), in unity (<strong>Around the World</strong>). 
            Then comes <strong>Transmission II</strong>: not a call from the past, but a renewed presence. 
            The pulse returns, stronger, more vivid. And yet, a shadow lingers (<strong>Shadows Return</strong>). 
            It is no longer mere technology – it is an entity, an energy feeding on the collective spirit.
          </div>
          <a href="#" class="listen-btn">Listen</a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Album 3 -->
      <article class="card">
        <div class="cover">
          <img src="uploads/album3.png" alt="Legacy of the Sentinel cover">
        </div>
        <div class="content">
          <div class="album-desc">
            The world now lives with its legacy. There is an <strong>Aftermath</strong>, scars of the past, and 
            <strong>Lost Signals</strong> still drifting in the ether. But the power of the Sentinel cannot be erased. 
            <strong>Transmission III</strong> resounds like a final message, a codex confronting humanity with its future. 
            The Sentinel is no longer seen solely as a threat, but as a mythical guardian. 
            Stories emerge of <strong>Guardians of the Grid</strong>, and temples of light (<strong>Temple of Neon</strong>) where people honor the pulse. 
            In the end, only a legacy remains: the memory of a mighty presence that never truly disappears – Legacy of the Sentinel.
          </div>
          <a href="#" class="listen-btn">Listen</a>
        </div>
      </article>
